Margins

INSTRUCTIONS: Give the div with the ID box a margin of 10 pixels at the top, 15 pixels on either side and 20 pixels on the bottom setting each margin individually (eg. margin-top: )

<!doctype html>
<html>
        <head>
        <title>Margins</title>
        <style type="text/css">
                        #box {
            }
        </style>
        </head>
    <body>
                <div id="box">Box</div>
    </body>
</html>


Answer:
<!doctype html>
<html>
        <head>
        <title>Margins</title>
        <style type="text/css">
            #box {
                margin-top:10px;
                margin-right:15px;
                margin-bottom:20px;
                margin-left:15px;
            }
        </style>
        </head>
    <body>
                <div id="box">Box</div>
    </body>
</html>